  "commentary": {
    "neutral_announcer_espn": "A lengthy rally unfolds, dominated by precise dinks exchanged at the kitchen line. The players demonstrate excellent control and patience, waiting for the opportune moment to strike. Ultimately, a slight miscalculation sends the final shot into the net, concluding the point.",
    "hype_announcer_charged": "WE'VE GOT A DINK-FEST GOING ON HERE! Back and forth, back and forth! These players are glued to the NVZ, painting the lines with those soft shots! Who's gonna blink first?! OH NO! The net monster claims another victim! A tough break to end a masterful display of touch!",
    "coaching_breakdown": "Notice the consistent depth and placement on the dinks from both players. They're effectively neutralizing each other's attack. The error came from trying to hit too close to the net on the final shot; a slightly deeper, softer dink might have been more effective, or looking for a transition zone drive if the opponent was too deep. Overall, good patience and control, but a need to develop more attacking options.",
